---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

const authorities = await getCollection('authorities');
const sortedAuthorities = authorities.sort((a, b) =>
  a.data.title.localeCompare(b.data.title)
);
---

<BaseLayout
  title="National Reference for Healthcare Pest Control Compliance"
  description="Authoritative reference work mapping U.S. federal, state, and accrediting body pest control compliance requirements for hospitals, critical access hospitals, skilled nursing facilities, ambulatory surgery centers, hospices, behavioral health, rehabilitation, and pediatric facilities. Primary-source anchored. Maintained by a Board Certified Entomologist."
>
  <h1>Healthcare Pest Reference</h1>

  <p>
    A national authoritative reference for healthcare pest control compliance. Maps the
    federal, state, accrediting body, and recognized authority requirements that govern
    pest management in U.S. healthcare facilities. Every requirement anchored to a
    primary source. Every fabricated or weakly-sourced claim that has been investigated
    and disconfirmed is explicitly labeled and excluded.
  </p>

  <p>
    The reference serves hospital facilities directors, infection preventionists, risk
    and compliance officers, Joint Commission and CMS survey readiness teams, healthcare
    procurement officers, plaintiff and defense attorneys litigating healthcare pest
    matters, and pest control operators serving healthcare clients.
  </p>

  <h2>Phase 1 — Federal Regulatory Anchors</h2>

  <p>
    Phase 1 of this reference covers the federal regulatory tier and the Utah state
    regulatory framework as a depth prototype. Subsequent phases will expand to the
    other 49 states, additional accrediting bodies (DNV-GL, HFAP, CIHQ), the FGI
    Guidelines for Design and Construction, and the institutional credentialing
    landscape across acute-care, critical access, skilled nursing, ambulatory surgery,
    hospice, behavioral health, rehabilitation, and pediatric facility types.
  </p>

  <h2>Current Authority Pages</h2>

  <ul>
    {sortedAuthorities.map(authority => (
      <li>
        <a href={`/authorities/${authority.slug}/`}>{authority.data.title}</a>
        {' '}— {authority.data.citation}
      </li>
    ))}
  </ul>

  <h2>How to Use This Reference</h2>

  <p>
    Each authority page is a self-contained explanation of one regulatory authority.
    Pages include the verbatim regulatory text where publicly available, a plain-language
    summary, the facility types the requirement applies to, the documentation evidence
    surveyors expect, the citation pathway surveyors use, and explicit notes on any
    adjacent claims that have been investigated and disconfirmed as fabricated or
    weakly sourced.
  </p>

  <p>
    Citations should be verified against the primary source for litigation-grade
    applications. The reference notes where primary sources are paywalled and
    institutional access is required for direct verbatim verification.
  </p>

  <h2>Methodology</h2>

  <p>
    Every fact in this reference is rated for source confidence and source tier.
    See the <a href="/methodology/">methodology page</a> for details on the verification
    discipline, the source tier hierarchy, and the explicit list of fabricated claims
    that have been investigated and excluded.
  </p>

  <p>
    The reference is maintained by Trenton L. Frazer, Board Certified Entomologist
    (BCE #B3413, General Entomology specialty), MS Entomology, University of Florida.
    See the <a href="/about/">about page</a> for credentialing detail and the reference's
    relationship to the operator's other work.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
